      "writtenOn": "2020-10-23T21:40:23Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "There\u0027s one way that you might be able to use to enforce it--not sure if it would work, but I can\u0027t think of any reason why not. Have the caller pass in the unique_ptr to the sub-statement but NOT extract it out from the node\u0027s statement. The ProgramVisitor is going to walk the statement tree, so have it detect that statement pointer as part of that walk. If it sees that statement pointer, skip over it; don\u0027t descend into that portion of the tree. If it doesn\u0027t detect it at all, then you need to do a usage-\u003eadd() on the new replacement statement (or assert if we explicitly don\u0027t want to support this).\n\nThis has the side benefit of not needing to support nulls in the program tree when walking it, since we don\u0027t ask the calling code to move it.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 38,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 39,
        "endChar": 69
      },
      "revId": "945c66e09183c4751873cd58b6646c42ba280203",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "e9a03125_07dd9bbf",
