      "writtenOn": "2020-10-26T13:59:34Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "For that to work, we\u0027d have to pass in std::unqiue_ptr\u003c\u003e*, then do std::move(*newStmt) inside setStatement, but it would work. (And the callers would be passing a pointer to the u_p, with the understanding that it\u0027s going to get moved. I\u0027m on the fence about that being clearer (though it does allow us to guard the API better). On the flip-side, I was thinking about just having debug-only code in the compiler that re-scans on each update, and asserts that all counts match between the incrementally maintained ones and a fresh scan.",
