      "writtenOn": "2020-10-26T13:59:34Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yup, that\u0027s a clearer version of what I was trying to convey. (Note that null is never passed in - the new null checks are because of the stolen sub-statement. We can now end up traversing a BinaryExpression with one of it\u0027s two children being null, for example).",
